WEBVTT

00:57.307 --> 00:58.516
I know who you are.

00:59.934 --> 01:00.977
You're Eun-u, right?

01:01.728 --> 01:03.104
How do you know me?

01:05.273 --> 01:06.483
How do I know you?

01:07.317 --> 01:08.359
Take a guess.

01:08.818 --> 01:10.695
Dad, who is she?

01:11.446 --> 01:12.906
Who do you think I am?

01:13.198 --> 01:14.074
Go ahead and guess.

01:19.370 --> 01:20.413
Mom?

01:24.375 --> 01:25.376
Why did you say that?

01:29.089 --> 01:30.215
I'm not scolding you.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.093
I said I'm not scolding you.

01:33.885 --> 01:34.844
Eun-u!

01:35.804 --> 01:37.263
There's no need for that.

01:41.184 --> 01:43.394
Eun-u, you like dinosaurs, right?

01:45.522 --> 01:47.690
That's what I heard. Am I wrong?

01:47.774 --> 01:49.901
I do like them.

01:52.237 --> 01:53.071
Ta-da.

01:55.740 --> 01:56.908
I have more.

01:59.869 --> 02:01.162
Let's see.

02:01.913 --> 02:04.249
Gosh,
look at all these different dinosaurs.

02:07.001 --> 02:08.753
Take a look. Here.

02:20.181 --> 02:21.891
Wow, how cool are those?

02:23.017 --> 02:24.853
- Excuse me.
- What's this one?

02:24.936 --> 02:26.646
It's a Spinosaurus.

02:27.480 --> 02:28.940
A Spinosaurus?

02:29.607 --> 02:31.776
- Ji-ho?
- What about this one?

02:32.277 --> 02:34.028
A Velociraptor.

02:34.612 --> 02:35.864
A Velociraptor?

02:38.783 --> 02:41.369
EPISODE 3

02:48.042 --> 02:49.127
I'm sorry.

02:50.712 --> 02:51.838
About what?

02:53.590 --> 02:56.634
He's never said that before.
I'm sure you were taken aback.

02:59.179 --> 03:01.973
I was. A lot, actually.

03:04.851 --> 03:07.020
I didn't know you were a mean dad.

03:09.981 --> 03:11.399
He made a mistake, so...

03:11.482 --> 03:14.819
Actually, you did.
It was nothing to get angry over.

03:15.945 --> 03:17.030
What do you...

03:17.405 --> 03:19.741
Not just spanking
is considered scolding.

03:19.824 --> 03:22.660
Do you normally get worked up
over small things?

03:22.785 --> 03:26.706
I knew you'd be flustered,
so I tried to remedy the situation.

03:27.373 --> 03:29.083
You thought I'd be grateful for that?

03:32.295 --> 03:34.756
- What?
- I didn't say anything.

03:35.882 --> 03:39.052
Even when I was a kid,
I thought it was unfair

03:39.135 --> 03:41.596
when adults interpreted
situations in their own way.

03:42.180 --> 03:44.891
When my parents did so,
I wanted to run away from home.

03:46.809 --> 03:49.312
Oh, no.
What if my son runs away from home?

03:51.314 --> 03:52.690
Apologize to him.

03:53.566 --> 03:55.360
He's fine now though.

03:55.860 --> 03:58.238
You think kids forget about
those hurtful comments?

03:58.321 --> 03:59.864
They remember everything.

04:00.448 --> 04:03.618
You don't want that pain
to turn him into a juvenile delinquent.

04:05.161 --> 04:06.120
Like someone I know?

04:09.457 --> 04:11.417
All right, fine. I'll apologize.

04:14.671 --> 04:16.589
I'd like to grab a cup of coffee with you.

04:18.800 --> 04:21.094
It's okay. You should stay with your son.

04:21.469 --> 04:23.096
I should get back to work, too.

04:23.972 --> 04:26.391
All right, then. Thank you for your time.

04:27.475 --> 04:28.601
It was no big deal.

04:45.034 --> 04:47.620
CHILDREN'S READING ROOM

04:56.254 --> 04:57.380
Where were you at?

04:57.463 --> 04:59.549
The stationery store out front.
What about you?

05:00.258 --> 05:02.135
Me? I just had a visitor.

05:02.218 --> 05:04.012
Right. Who was he again?

05:04.679 --> 05:06.681
I know him from somewhere.

05:07.890 --> 05:09.809
- He's the pharmacist.
- That's right!

05:11.686 --> 05:12.979
How do you know him, though?

05:13.604 --> 05:15.690
He's an alumnus of Gi-seok's university.

05:15.773 --> 05:19.068
I see. I was wondering
who the new guy was.

05:21.654 --> 05:22.905
You and your imagination.

05:22.989 --> 05:26.034
You haven't been
your usual self these days.

05:26.117 --> 05:26.993
Of course I have.

05:28.244 --> 05:30.371
No, something's definitely up.

05:30.455 --> 05:32.582
- What?
- You're acting strange.

05:33.291 --> 05:34.208
Eun-u.

05:36.336 --> 05:37.337
Yes?

05:39.839 --> 05:41.132
Can you look at me?

05:43.676 --> 05:45.720
I'm sorry about before.

05:46.262 --> 05:47.388
Why are you sorry?

05:51.893 --> 05:55.938
I got angry with you
even though you did nothing wrong.

05:57.023 --> 05:59.192
That's why I'm very sorry.

05:59.901 --> 06:00.943
All right.

06:02.695 --> 06:03.780
Are you forgiving me?

06:04.739 --> 06:05.823
Of course.

06:06.908 --> 06:08.159
Why is that?

06:08.743 --> 06:09.952
Because you're my dad.

06:21.964 --> 06:23.466
RECIPIENT: NAM SI-HOON

06:23.549 --> 06:25.176
FINAL NOTICE

06:33.893 --> 06:38.231
The alumni committee manager has skills.
How did you book a hotel for the reunion?

06:38.314 --> 06:41.234
It's the first one I'm planning,
and it's for the entire alumni.

06:42.068 --> 06:44.987
Dong-jun is letting me
host the party at his hotel as a donation.

06:46.739 --> 06:48.282
That was generous for a scrooge.

06:48.950 --> 06:51.536
Your brother and brother-in-law
donated five million won.

06:52.537 --> 06:54.622
Both their hospitals must be doing well.

06:57.208 --> 06:59.252
You should make a contribution, too--

06:59.335 --> 07:01.295
- How about ten million won?
- What?

07:02.046 --> 07:03.131
Really?

07:05.049 --> 07:07.176
There's no need to go all out, you know.

07:07.260 --> 07:09.554
It's not that much,
so shut up and take your shot.

07:09.637 --> 07:10.847
Are you sure about this?

07:10.930 --> 07:13.558
A manager of the alumni committee
should know how to party.

07:13.641 --> 07:14.559
It's my wife.

07:16.144 --> 07:17.854
- I'll go and answer this.
- Sure.

07:17.937 --> 07:19.105
- Take your shot.
- Got it.

07:24.944 --> 07:26.779
It's no big deal, so rip the damn thing.

07:27.363 --> 07:28.531
Change your address.

07:29.073 --> 07:32.743
I told you that I'm not going
to stay separated for long.

07:33.077 --> 07:35.872
Switch it back to your father's place.
Should I do it for you?

07:36.873 --> 07:39.834
I see that your brain has been busy.

07:39.917 --> 07:42.879
Are you using my parents as leverage?
Fine, go for it.

07:43.171 --> 07:44.839
I'd like to see what you tell them--

07:44.922 --> 07:47.091
- I'm selling the house.
- What did you just say?

07:49.469 --> 07:50.553
Sure.

07:51.721 --> 07:52.889
Try that, too.

07:53.222 --> 07:55.725
Let's see how long
you can stay hidden from me.

07:57.351 --> 07:58.269
- Gi-seok.
- Yes?

07:59.061 --> 08:02.231
When do you actually go on dates?

08:05.526 --> 08:08.863
My girlfriend works at a library,
so she doesn't always get weekends off.

08:09.572 --> 08:11.491
She works late hours during the week, too.

08:13.326 --> 08:16.621
The lack of time spent together
is why you've been dating for so long.

08:18.664 --> 08:19.707
It's not bad, though.

08:20.291 --> 08:23.127
A passionate relationship
can easily dwindle away.

08:23.878 --> 08:25.922
You shouldn't date someone for too long.

08:26.422 --> 08:27.465
Why not?

08:28.174 --> 08:29.634
There's nothing good about it.

08:31.385 --> 08:35.723
You and your girlfriend
already look like a married couple anyway.

08:38.893 --> 08:41.437
You aren't one of those
cringe-worthy couples.

08:41.521 --> 08:44.815
Did you expect us to show public displays
of affection in front of you?

08:44.899 --> 08:46.192
Do you do so in private?

08:48.903 --> 08:49.904
Unbelievable.

08:51.197 --> 08:53.032
It's weird to still be like that anyway.

08:53.115 --> 08:56.494
How's that weird?
All couples in love are like that.

09:00.122 --> 09:03.543
Yes, exactly. That is quite important.

09:04.460 --> 09:08.548
No physical response means
that there are no feelings left.

09:09.882 --> 09:11.842
Think of the opposite, though.

09:12.843 --> 09:15.596
The response will be involuntary.

09:41.831 --> 09:42.873
Hello.

09:47.837 --> 09:49.839
CHILDREN'S READING ROOM

10:46.979 --> 10:48.022
Eun-u.

10:50.274 --> 10:51.901
- Yu Eun-u?
- Yes?

10:54.695 --> 10:56.197
Back at the library...

10:59.617 --> 11:00.785
Can you look at me?

11:03.079 --> 11:04.205
Why did you...

11:05.998 --> 11:07.208
ask if she was your mom?

11:10.252 --> 11:12.880
Can you tell me why you said that?

11:13.422 --> 11:14.965
I won't anymore.

11:19.136 --> 11:20.888
I'm not saying you did anything wrong.

11:21.681 --> 11:23.641
You've never mentioned your mom before,

11:23.724 --> 11:25.643
so I'm just curious.

11:41.701 --> 11:42.952
Did he already fall asleep?

11:44.829 --> 11:46.205
He must've been exhausted.

11:49.417 --> 11:52.962
Why did you buy him more books when
there are still many he hasn't read yet?

11:53.587 --> 11:55.756
- Someone gave them to him.
- Who?

11:59.301 --> 12:01.387
Don't you want anything to eat, then?

12:02.138 --> 12:03.681
We ate before leaving the library.

12:05.850 --> 12:07.184
Leave your stuff and join us.

12:35.171 --> 12:36.422
No, a bit lower.

12:42.470 --> 12:43.596
Is it acting up again?

12:44.680 --> 12:46.557
This is common for people our age.

12:47.808 --> 12:50.978
If you're not going to stay the night,
go before it gets too late.

12:56.692 --> 12:57.818
Has Eun-u...

12:59.028 --> 13:00.446
ever mentioned his mom?

13:00.529 --> 13:01.572
What mom?

13:03.115 --> 13:04.074
His mom?

13:05.618 --> 13:07.453
Why? Did he say something?

13:08.120 --> 13:10.623
I'm just asking. Did he say anything?

13:11.665 --> 13:14.168
He's never been the type
to ask such questions.

13:14.251 --> 13:15.795
What's going on?

13:16.462 --> 13:18.798
It's just that he'll ask someday.

13:19.965 --> 13:21.675
There's nothing to hide or sugarcoat.

13:22.218 --> 13:25.429
When he's a little older,
tell him the full story.

13:25.846 --> 13:27.932
Still, we can't...

13:28.015 --> 13:30.226
It's better than making something up.

13:31.560 --> 13:36.357
The same goes for you, too.
Be honest with whomever you date.

13:36.941 --> 13:38.317
My life isn't that important.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.778
How is it not just as important?

13:41.529 --> 13:43.239
You can't stay single all your life.

13:45.491 --> 13:47.243
Some parents even abandon their kids,

13:47.326 --> 13:49.036
so you're admirable compared to them.

13:49.453 --> 13:51.622
- Mom, please don't.
- You love your boy, right?

13:52.289 --> 13:54.291
Well, I love mine just as much.

13:54.375 --> 13:56.210
Enough with the nonsense.

13:57.962 --> 13:59.046
You should get going.

14:01.924 --> 14:05.052
Whenever it may be,
I'd like to tell him about his mom, so--

14:05.135 --> 14:06.887
Of course. There's no need to worry.

14:10.766 --> 14:13.269
- I'll get going, then.
- What did Eun-u say?

14:13.352 --> 14:15.271
Just let the boy go home.

14:16.772 --> 14:18.148
Get going, Ji-ho.

14:34.665 --> 14:35.958
I'll be back on the weekend.

14:36.500 --> 14:39.003
Do what you have to do.
Don't be obliged to always come.

14:39.420 --> 14:42.381
I've got nothing going on.
Call me if something comes up.

14:43.340 --> 14:45.217
Your mom and I aren't that old yet.

14:46.468 --> 14:47.887
Anyway, don't skip your meals.

14:50.180 --> 14:51.181
I won't.

14:52.141 --> 14:53.183
Good night.

15:24.673 --> 15:26.216
You're the pharmacist, right?

15:27.885 --> 15:29.219
Do you live in this building?

15:29.803 --> 15:31.055
Yes, on the third floor.

15:32.181 --> 15:35.726
Oh, I see.

15:36.310 --> 15:37.478
How interesting.

15:40.814 --> 15:42.358
- Good night, then.
- Bye.

15:42.775 --> 15:43.776
Bye.

15:52.910 --> 15:55.079
Lee Jeong-in, you're dead meat.

15:59.959 --> 16:01.001
Let's see.

16:18.894 --> 16:21.105
Not even celebrities wear those indoors.

16:22.272 --> 16:23.649
What's with the illustrations?

16:26.151 --> 16:28.445
It's for children.
I guess I bought the wrong kind.

16:29.154 --> 16:30.489
But you don't even like kids.

16:31.115 --> 16:32.324
Why don't I like kids?

16:33.659 --> 16:34.952
Is it Seo-in who hates them?

16:36.203 --> 16:37.454
She knows you're in Korea.

16:39.790 --> 16:42.376
You two always talked behind my back.

16:43.252 --> 16:46.005
Just be glad that
we haven't told Mom and Dad.

16:46.797 --> 16:48.090
When do you want to see her?

16:50.676 --> 16:52.344
When Si-hoon isn't around.

16:54.138 --> 16:56.265
You've never really liked him. Why?

16:57.182 --> 16:58.100
No reason.

16:59.643 --> 17:01.145
That's how some people are.

17:01.228 --> 17:04.314
Some you just hate,
while some you're fond of for no reason.

17:14.700 --> 17:15.826
Thank you for the book

17:16.952 --> 17:18.245
and also for being a friend.

17:19.621 --> 17:20.956
You must really love Gi-seok.

17:21.457 --> 17:23.125
Want to see how you smiled just now?

17:29.006 --> 17:30.340
It's not a big deal.

18:08.253 --> 18:10.422
- You do it.
- I can't. I'm too scared.

18:10.506 --> 18:11.590
I did it last time.

18:12.341 --> 18:13.759
Good morning, sir.

18:15.844 --> 18:16.929
Any appointments today?

18:18.138 --> 18:19.473
There's one in the afternoon.

18:21.058 --> 18:22.059
Sir.

18:23.977 --> 18:26.814
There's a letter of notice
regarding this month's overdue rent.

19:06.019 --> 19:07.354
- Hello?
- Hi, it's me.

19:07.437 --> 19:08.397
Hi.

19:09.481 --> 19:10.774
- How--
- How have you been?

19:11.108 --> 19:13.569
You know me.
I'm always busy with patients.

19:15.154 --> 19:18.323
So what's up with you?
I haven't seen you around much.

19:18.699 --> 19:21.076
I've been busy helping
people get divorced.

19:21.618 --> 19:24.913
Is that so? Are there that many couples
that take their divorce to court?

19:25.122 --> 19:28.500
Divorce attorneys
must be hitting the jackpot.

19:29.835 --> 19:31.795
- So what's the occasion?
- Oh, well...

19:33.088 --> 19:36.800
I was just wondering about
what I could do with my house.

19:36.884 --> 19:40.053
The property is under her name, too.
Would it be harder to sell?

19:40.137 --> 19:42.514
It's not that complicated.
Are you getting a divorce?

19:44.224 --> 19:48.353
Seriously? If I were,
would you give me a discount?

19:50.439 --> 19:54.026
Actually, I'm thinking about
moving to a bigger house.

19:55.235 --> 19:58.655
Take your cues from me, my friend.
If only all husbands were like me.

19:58.739 --> 20:01.033
I'm trying to sell it myself
since my wife is busy.

20:09.958 --> 20:11.168
Hey, that was quick.

20:11.793 --> 20:12.794
Have a seat.

20:18.050 --> 20:20.886
It's a new show
that'll be airing next month.

20:23.847 --> 20:27.184
Just think of it as a news magazine on TV.

20:29.186 --> 20:30.562
You'll be the sole host.

20:32.022 --> 20:33.023
Me?

20:33.732 --> 20:36.985
It airs at 6:00 p.m., so we will be
targeting middle-aged men and women.

20:37.069 --> 20:39.613
You have a gentle and clean image.

20:43.742 --> 20:45.661
A chance like this doesn't come by easily.

20:47.454 --> 20:49.414
- I'm aware.
- Then why the sour face?

20:49.498 --> 20:50.791
That's not the case.

20:51.416 --> 20:52.751
It's just sudden, that's all.

20:54.044 --> 20:55.879
That's the nature of opportunities.

20:56.755 --> 20:58.632
Although it's only for those prepared.

21:25.534 --> 21:28.036
- Hello?
- This is Golden Real Estate.

21:29.121 --> 21:33.333
Your apartment unit is being held
as collateral for your bank debt.

21:33.834 --> 21:34.751
That's right.

21:34.835 --> 21:39.256
I called to ask you about how you want
to sell the place.

21:42.217 --> 21:46.013
I'll discuss it with my husband
and call you back.

21:46.763 --> 21:49.683
Sure thing.
Let me know what you decide, then.

21:49.766 --> 21:50.976
Thank you.

22:30.932 --> 22:32.309
I can do this by myself.

22:36.438 --> 22:37.522
What now?

22:38.440 --> 22:39.483
The pharmacist.

22:40.942 --> 22:42.235
What are you talking about?

22:43.111 --> 22:44.196
Third floor.

22:46.698 --> 22:48.033
Why did you lie about him?

22:48.742 --> 22:49.826
I didn't lie.

22:53.747 --> 22:54.915
What are you doing?

22:57.501 --> 23:00.170
I should ask him myself
on my way home today.

23:00.879 --> 23:01.922
Hey!

23:03.757 --> 23:04.800
Wait...

23:05.342 --> 23:06.468
Hold up. Hey!

23:07.928 --> 23:08.970
My gosh.

23:10.263 --> 23:11.098
What now?

23:11.598 --> 23:12.641
What?

23:13.141 --> 23:16.228
He's just an alumnus
of Gi-seok's university.

23:17.145 --> 23:18.897
Why are you being so cautious, though?

23:19.398 --> 23:21.525
I don't want you to make a big deal
out of it.

23:21.608 --> 23:23.652
You're the one who's making a fuss here.

23:23.735 --> 23:24.986
What are you talking about?

23:26.154 --> 23:27.614
I knew something was up.

23:28.573 --> 23:29.950
It's not what you think.

23:30.575 --> 23:32.119
And what is it that I think?

23:36.331 --> 23:37.541
We agreed to be friends.

23:38.792 --> 23:39.918
Just friends.

23:42.629 --> 23:44.005
There's no harm in that.

23:47.843 --> 23:49.428
Because that's all you could be?

23:52.722 --> 23:54.099
Jeong-in, you...

23:55.058 --> 23:57.477
This is some big trouble you're in.

23:59.187 --> 24:00.480
This is bad.

24:03.316 --> 24:04.651
Forget that I know anything.

24:07.404 --> 24:08.572
What...

24:27.424 --> 24:29.676
I'll take that off your hands.
You have a visitor.

24:36.766 --> 24:37.767
Hey.

24:41.021 --> 24:42.230
What brings you here?

24:42.898 --> 24:45.192
To get medicine.
Why else would I be at a pharmacy?

24:45.734 --> 24:47.819
You'd treat me well
since I'm a familiar face.

24:49.321 --> 24:50.530
How can I help you?

24:50.614 --> 24:54.701
Do you have anything that relieves stress?

24:55.243 --> 24:58.747
My girlfriend's been on edge these days.

25:01.833 --> 25:04.669
Can you recommend me some vitamins?

25:05.629 --> 25:08.256
Do you also have anything for elders?

25:08.340 --> 25:09.716
I'd like that, as well.

25:10.550 --> 25:11.551
Hold on a second.

25:16.848 --> 25:18.558
Why don't you take a seat?

25:18.642 --> 25:19.809
Sure thing.

25:23.188 --> 25:24.022
Ji-ho.

25:25.273 --> 25:27.484
Price isn't an issue, so recommend away.

25:43.250 --> 25:44.834
Why don't you stay for a meal?

25:45.585 --> 25:49.047
The sooner I kiss up to her, the better.
Things are that cold between us.

25:49.339 --> 25:50.465
Why's that?

25:52.801 --> 25:53.927
I'm not even sure.

25:54.010 --> 25:57.013
Maybe it's because
we're talking about marriage.

25:58.098 --> 25:59.307
Are you getting married?

26:00.892 --> 26:03.436
Soon. We've been dating for a while.

26:05.522 --> 26:07.232
- Congratulations.
- Not yet.

26:07.857 --> 26:10.652
It's too soon for that, though.
The idea is fairly new.

26:12.654 --> 26:14.072
Anyway, thank you for these

26:14.155 --> 26:17.200
and giving me the discount.
Are you sure it's not a loss for you?

26:17.284 --> 26:18.285
It's fine.

26:21.162 --> 26:24.082
We should get together
either on the basketball court

26:24.165 --> 26:26.626
or maybe for some drinks with Hyeon-su.
It'll be on me.

26:28.044 --> 26:29.045
Sure.

26:30.171 --> 26:32.215
You should head inside. Thanks again.

26:34.551 --> 26:35.927
You should get going.

27:07.500 --> 27:08.627
Good night, guys.

27:10.045 --> 27:11.129
See you tomorrow.

27:20.680 --> 27:22.932
They graduated the same university, right?

27:23.016 --> 27:26.227
Yes. He hasn't really been himself
since that man stopped by, right?

27:26.311 --> 27:27.312
Yes, totally.

27:27.395 --> 27:29.648
He gave him a discount, though.
They seemed close.

27:29.731 --> 27:32.692
I know all his close friends,
but I've never seen that man before.

27:33.026 --> 27:34.778
- It's odd.
- What's odd?

27:35.862 --> 27:38.365
Ji-ho never gets mood swings like that.

29:07.662 --> 29:09.164
Oh, another picture.

29:09.539 --> 29:12.625
This little pumpkin is bringing
so much joy into my life these days.

29:12.917 --> 29:15.295
She's three,
but she can read pretty much everything.

29:16.296 --> 29:17.839
It sounds like she's a genius.

29:19.424 --> 29:21.551
What kid isn't a genius?

29:22.302 --> 29:24.095
My granddaughter is different.

29:24.554 --> 29:26.431
Tae-hak, please believe me.

29:26.514 --> 29:28.308
- Goodness.
- Of course, I believe you.

29:29.434 --> 29:33.188
By the way, when are you two
going to become in-laws?

29:33.688 --> 29:35.398
Why haven't we heard any updates yet?

29:35.607 --> 29:37.567
We have no updates to give you.

29:38.735 --> 29:41.488
Did they break up, by any chance?

29:41.863 --> 29:43.156
What are you talking about?

29:43.239 --> 29:46.159
They're very happy in their relationship.
Don't say such a thing.

29:48.495 --> 29:51.998
Young people these days
are just on the ball.

29:52.081 --> 29:55.126
Leave it to them,
and they'll figure out everything.

29:56.377 --> 29:57.420
Yes, exactly.

29:59.631 --> 30:02.509
I wouldn't believe that.

30:02.759 --> 30:04.260
They'll just keep getting old.

30:04.803 --> 30:06.262
I've seen it many times.

30:06.763 --> 30:09.098
Right, they should end it
before that happens.

30:09.641 --> 30:12.018
They shouldn't be a roadblock
in each other's lives.

30:12.560 --> 30:14.395
- Let me--
- No, it's all right.

30:20.610 --> 30:23.196
You went all the way there to buy this?

30:24.614 --> 30:26.449
Do you think I went there to see Ji-ho?

30:27.992 --> 30:30.870
But he gave me so much discount.
I guess he felt like he had to.

30:32.622 --> 30:33.915
Why did you go there?

30:34.749 --> 30:35.875
Because of you.

30:38.336 --> 30:42.048
You've been overly sensitive,
so I thought those vitamins might help.

30:44.300 --> 30:46.302
I asked him for stress relievers.

30:47.554 --> 30:49.347
I hope they work.

30:51.641 --> 30:52.642
Gosh.

30:55.019 --> 30:56.646
By the way, Ji-ho has a kid.

30:59.107 --> 31:00.984
- He told you that?
- No, Hyeon-su told me.

31:02.777 --> 31:06.698
He met the mom at a young age,
but she left after having the baby.

31:08.992 --> 31:10.285
What do you mean?

31:11.619 --> 31:12.829
Just as you heard.

31:14.372 --> 31:16.791
He can't even find her
because she left the country.

31:21.421 --> 31:23.715
I guess he can meet someone
in a similar situation.

31:26.301 --> 31:29.012
He shouldn't limit himself.
Having a kid isn't a crime.

31:29.095 --> 31:31.556
Right. But it'll be best,
even for his own sake.

31:32.265 --> 31:33.641
Why be the only flawed one?

31:37.145 --> 31:38.438
He should've done better.

31:38.730 --> 31:40.315
What did he do to make her leave?

31:41.399 --> 31:43.026
Would that have changed things?

31:45.653 --> 31:46.654
What's the matter now?

31:47.697 --> 31:48.698
Well...

31:49.532 --> 31:51.701
Doing better or not isn't the issue here.

31:52.660 --> 31:53.912
Feelings have changed.

31:59.208 --> 32:00.460
What's with that stare?

32:04.714 --> 32:05.757
Nothing.

32:09.886 --> 32:10.929
You should go in.

32:11.554 --> 32:12.931
Jae-in must be waiting.

32:13.973 --> 32:16.893
Make sure you take this
even if it feels like a hassle.

32:17.560 --> 32:19.938
And give this to your parents, okay?

32:22.523 --> 32:24.400
Thanks. I'll make sure to take it.

32:24.484 --> 32:25.568
All right.

32:26.277 --> 32:27.445
- Drive safely.
- Okay.

32:30.114 --> 32:32.033
- Get some rest.
- All right.

32:45.380 --> 32:46.673
The door is opening.

32:48.508 --> 32:51.260
- Hey, where are you going?
- I'm going out for some good food.

32:51.344 --> 32:53.221
- With who?
- With a friend. See you later.

32:53.304 --> 32:55.431
- Which friend?
- Stop acting like you're my mom.

32:56.265 --> 32:57.392
Don't stay out too late.

33:39.475 --> 33:40.518
Hey.

33:40.977 --> 33:42.562
Should we have had a cup of coffee?

33:44.272 --> 33:45.398
No, it's getting late.

33:45.982 --> 33:47.191
Who cares?

33:48.109 --> 33:49.235
Shall I come by now?

33:51.362 --> 33:53.948
Not today. Jae-in is here, you know.

33:57.243 --> 33:59.037
- Gi-seok.
- Right.

34:00.788 --> 34:01.998
Okay. Get some rest, then.

35:50.523 --> 35:51.566
Hello?

35:52.733 --> 35:53.901
It's me, Lee Jeong-in.

35:54.610 --> 35:55.653
Yes.

35:57.280 --> 35:58.614
I got the vitamins.

36:05.997 --> 36:07.331
Hello?

36:08.541 --> 36:10.918
So, this is what your voice sounds like
on the phone.

36:14.297 --> 36:15.548
Hello?

36:17.633 --> 36:18.676
Go ahead.

36:19.343 --> 36:20.636
I shouldn't have said that.

36:23.014 --> 36:24.807
So, should I forget it? Like last time?

36:27.059 --> 36:28.811
Well, you told me that's not possible.

36:29.520 --> 36:31.814
I said it
since it's our first phone conversation.

36:32.899 --> 36:35.443
So? How does my voice sound?

36:39.447 --> 36:40.656
It sounds all right.

36:40.740 --> 36:42.658
Your voice isn't that nice, either.

36:44.368 --> 36:45.661
I guess I dug my own grave.

36:47.413 --> 36:49.040
I see you can crack jokes.

36:50.249 --> 36:51.459
I didn't think you could.

36:53.753 --> 36:54.962
I'm actually pretty funny.

36:56.088 --> 36:57.131
How so?

36:57.924 --> 36:59.634
People used to tell me that a lot.

37:02.261 --> 37:05.014
So, you're not like that anymore?

37:05.932 --> 37:08.142
Or did you intentionally change
your personality?

37:10.144 --> 37:11.229
I'm not sure...

37:11.938 --> 37:14.065
whether it was intentional or not.

37:15.107 --> 37:16.609
Or do I just not have the chance?

37:17.735 --> 37:19.070
I'll listen to your jokes.

37:20.029 --> 37:21.197
We're friends, you know.

37:23.658 --> 37:25.117
Can you afford to do that?

37:26.118 --> 37:27.620
Aren't you under a lot of stress?

37:30.164 --> 37:31.791
I'm just a little tired these days.

37:40.758 --> 37:42.093
Are you getting another call?

37:44.262 --> 37:45.930
Yes. I'm sorry.

37:47.598 --> 37:48.683
It's all right.

37:50.643 --> 37:51.686
Goodbye, then.

38:30.850 --> 38:32.351
Hello.

38:34.228 --> 38:37.023
Well, I'm just here to drop off
some side dishes.

38:37.106 --> 38:39.275
- I see.
- When my daughter gets in, tell her...

38:39.358 --> 38:40.234
Sure.

38:44.071 --> 38:45.281
Jae-in?

38:49.660 --> 38:51.245
What are you doing here?

38:53.247 --> 38:54.248
Hey.

38:56.292 --> 38:57.793
I asked you why you're here.

39:02.089 --> 39:04.925
I dropped out of the program
and moved back.

39:08.054 --> 39:09.930
- Mom! I'm sorry!
- Have you gone mad?

39:10.014 --> 39:11.349
- Are you nuts?
- Mom, it hurts!

39:11.432 --> 39:13.351
- I said it hurts!
- Have you lost your mind?

39:13.434 --> 39:16.228
- Mom, please.
- This is crazy. How could you do that?

39:17.271 --> 39:21.192
You should never open your own pharmacy
because you're too generous.

39:21.275 --> 39:22.526
The same goes for marriage!

39:22.610 --> 39:25.029
You always do things
that women would absolutely hate.

39:25.446 --> 39:27.907
Ye-seul, would women be turned off
by a man like me--

39:27.990 --> 39:29.325
Yes, totally. Big time!

39:31.619 --> 39:33.204
Goodness, he's still smiling.

39:34.288 --> 39:36.791
- We're off.
- All right. Get home safely.

39:40.336 --> 39:41.420
- Bye.
- Bye.

39:41.504 --> 39:43.506
- Hello.
- Oh, hello. Have a nice dinner.

39:43.589 --> 39:44.840
- We will. Thank you.
- Bye.

39:49.220 --> 39:50.346
- Hey, you're here.
- Yes.

39:51.347 --> 39:52.348
Give me a minute.

39:55.142 --> 39:55.976
How do you...

40:00.356 --> 40:01.482
- This...
- Yes.

40:01.565 --> 40:03.067
...can be sent just like this.

40:03.943 --> 40:05.945
Oh, that thing.
Hey, how much do I owe you?

40:07.321 --> 40:08.864
How much? Hey, don't do this.

40:08.948 --> 40:11.534
My mom will yell at me
for never paying for these things.

40:12.118 --> 40:13.244
Who says it's free?

40:13.327 --> 40:15.621
I'll mooch off you
when you become a civil servant.

40:16.330 --> 40:17.748
Gosh, seriously.

40:18.082 --> 40:20.376
Oh, right.
I saw that person on my way here.

40:20.459 --> 40:22.878
The guy who went
to the same university as you...

40:23.712 --> 40:25.506
- You mean, Gi-seok?
- His girlfriend.

40:27.633 --> 40:29.885
- Where did you see her?
- Near the bus stop.

40:29.969 --> 40:32.346
She was with a group of people,
so I didn't say hi.

40:41.564 --> 40:43.023
Has Jae-in called you recently?

40:44.525 --> 40:45.818
I think she's doing well.

40:46.485 --> 40:48.737
What kind of answer is that? Call her now.

40:49.655 --> 40:51.991
Gosh, she's probably studying.
Let's not bother her.

40:52.575 --> 40:54.326
You said I should call her more often.

40:54.910 --> 40:55.995
Just call her!

40:56.787 --> 40:59.957
I scolded her earlier.
I told her to focus and study harder,

41:00.040 --> 41:01.417
so she's mad at me now.

41:01.959 --> 41:03.794
You baby them when they need a scolding.

41:04.378 --> 41:06.964
I'm afraid Jeong-in's wedding
may turn out like Seo-in's.

41:08.257 --> 41:09.967
What about Seo-in's wedding?

41:10.259 --> 41:12.386
You didn't even let either of us speak up.

41:13.137 --> 41:14.430
You coddled her.

41:14.763 --> 41:17.099
And that's why she's still mad at me.

41:20.060 --> 41:22.521
If you were going to miss
having them around,

41:22.605 --> 41:25.107
you should've been
more affectionate with them.

41:25.191 --> 41:26.525
Why regret now?

41:27.359 --> 41:29.028
Have some shame.

42:08.901 --> 42:12.071
You said you were leaving work
when I texted you. Did you just get in?

42:12.488 --> 42:15.533
No, I fell asleep for a few minutes.

42:16.450 --> 42:19.161
Shouldn't you be all ready
to greet your baby sister?

42:21.288 --> 42:22.915
Look at that brazen attitude.

42:24.083 --> 42:25.501
I won't cry over spilled milk.

42:26.752 --> 42:28.003
Mom knows I'm in Korea now.

42:29.630 --> 42:30.714
Well done.

42:31.423 --> 42:33.300
So? What's your plan now?

42:34.885 --> 42:38.722
Are you going to get me a job
if I tell you my plan?

42:40.808 --> 42:42.184
Does the company pay well?

42:58.742 --> 42:59.827
Spend mindfully.

43:00.953 --> 43:02.454
Thank you!

43:05.249 --> 43:07.710
- By the way, where's Si-hoon?
- He'll be home late.

43:10.337 --> 43:12.631
I should leave before he gets home.

43:14.425 --> 43:15.884
Why do you hate him so much?

43:19.096 --> 43:20.556
He doesn't know how to love you.

43:26.854 --> 43:28.564
I'm going to make myself some coffee.

43:36.030 --> 43:39.783
I'm sorry, Si-hoon.
I feel like I never call you first.

43:39.867 --> 43:41.577
Gosh, who cares?

43:44.955 --> 43:46.749
You and Jeong-in are good, right?

43:47.708 --> 43:49.627
Yes.
We're obviously still together, but...

43:51.253 --> 43:52.588
Are you guys having problems?

43:55.174 --> 43:56.008
Well...

43:57.384 --> 43:59.595
I guess getting married
takes a lot of work.

44:02.097 --> 44:03.432
Did you feel the same way?

44:06.727 --> 44:09.313
Every daughter in that family
can be quite a handful.

44:15.319 --> 44:17.946
We should all get together.
I'll give her a little push.

44:20.949 --> 44:24.161
The thing is, it's not easy
to find a time that works for Jeong-in,

44:24.244 --> 44:27.081
and I've been busier
since I transferred to the new department.

44:28.165 --> 44:30.209
The evaluation team, right?
Are you that busy?

44:31.669 --> 44:33.837
We just have to take care
of a lot of paperwork.

44:34.755 --> 44:36.215
The regulations have changed,

44:36.298 --> 44:38.801
so there are now more things to look at
to grant loans.

44:39.218 --> 44:43.555
Jeez. Had I known,
I would've taken out a loan ahead of time.

44:45.057 --> 44:46.475
Do you need to take out a loan?

44:47.601 --> 44:49.895
Well,
I'm thinking of expanding the clinic.

44:49.978 --> 44:51.438
We keep getting more patients,

44:51.522 --> 44:54.149
and because I want to provide
better service, I'm torn.

44:55.776 --> 44:56.944
What do you think?

45:00.447 --> 45:03.158
Well, I'm not sure.
I don't know much about the industry.

45:05.077 --> 45:08.330
You know how I am.
I hate having to take out a loan.

45:12.459 --> 45:15.504
Even if it's stressful,
you will marry Jeong-in, right?

45:17.631 --> 45:18.924
Yes, we should get married.

45:21.635 --> 45:24.638
Tell me whenever it gets stressful.
I'll help in any way I can.

45:24.722 --> 45:25.889
Okay, thank you.

45:28.225 --> 45:29.351
Here, let me do it.

45:33.731 --> 45:35.441
I won't need all those things, right?

45:37.693 --> 45:41.280
Come on. We're practically family, right?

45:41.739 --> 45:45.284
It'd be nice if you could simplify
the evaluation process for me, you know.

45:47.786 --> 45:49.246
- Cheers.
- Yes.

45:50.581 --> 45:52.750
Text me a list of documents
that are imperative.

45:55.169 --> 45:56.336
- Drink up.
- Okay.

45:56.712 --> 45:57.838
This is on me.

46:08.474 --> 46:09.391
I'll be right back.

46:11.810 --> 46:13.270
We'd like to settle up.

46:13.353 --> 46:16.482
Oh, sure. For the two bowls of noodles,
your total is 13,500 won.

46:18.525 --> 46:20.319
- Here you go.
- Perfect.

46:20.402 --> 46:21.695
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

46:26.366 --> 46:27.910
You're not buying me a drink?

46:28.619 --> 46:30.704
Do you want a drink?
We can go somewhere else--

46:30.788 --> 46:33.165
It's all right.
Just go home and study, dude.

46:38.545 --> 46:40.923
Are you seeing anyone these days?

46:41.590 --> 46:44.968
Do you want to be punched in the face?
You know I can't afford to date now.

46:47.095 --> 46:48.305
It's not like I can.

46:52.226 --> 46:53.560
Like Hyeon-su said,

46:54.728 --> 46:56.146
you should start dating again.

46:56.730 --> 46:58.065
I don't want to do anything.

46:59.900 --> 47:01.902
You need to think about Eun-u as well.

47:04.530 --> 47:06.448
I don't want to find a nanny.

47:08.492 --> 47:09.535
And I shouldn't.

47:09.618 --> 47:11.787
- Well, that's not what I meant--
- In any case...

47:13.455 --> 47:18.085
If I ever meet someone who I can see
myself getting romantically involved with,

47:19.336 --> 47:20.712
then I'll think about it.

47:32.307 --> 47:34.476
Actually,
there was someone I wanted to date.

47:36.478 --> 47:37.771
Who? Who was it?

47:37.855 --> 47:41.650
You... Hey, dude.
Was it someone Hyeon-su and I know?

47:44.695 --> 47:46.822
What happened? Why didn't you date her?

47:51.827 --> 47:53.954
Her voice didn't sound that nice
on the phone.

47:54.830 --> 47:55.873
Oh, really?

47:56.540 --> 47:57.583
Cut the crap.

47:58.792 --> 48:00.168
Just eat your food, dude.

48:04.715 --> 48:05.716
What was that about?

48:08.802 --> 48:11.305
Hey, are you listening to me right now?

48:11.388 --> 48:15.517
Stop eating and focus on my story, please!
You've been stuffing your face...

48:15.601 --> 48:17.394
- Hello.
- It's delicious.

48:17.477 --> 48:18.604
You can take that table.

48:33.702 --> 48:35.871
- Hello?
- Are you out drinking?

48:48.425 --> 48:49.843
Why are you standing there?

48:51.678 --> 48:53.180
I'm just on my way home.

48:57.643 --> 48:58.810
Did you just leave work?

48:59.227 --> 49:00.562
No, I was with a friend.

49:01.855 --> 49:03.941
I guess you guys called it an early night.

49:04.024 --> 49:05.275
Good boy.

49:09.780 --> 49:12.240
By the way, why did you call me?

49:15.535 --> 49:17.871
I happened to see you on my way home,

49:19.039 --> 49:21.166
and I wanted to hear your voice.

49:25.921 --> 49:27.005
Ji-ho.

49:29.633 --> 49:31.843
- You see, we should--
- I know we're just friends.

49:34.972 --> 49:38.016
Don't worry. I won't cross the line.

49:42.688 --> 49:46.191
If things like this make you
uncomfortable, I won't do it anymore.

49:52.239 --> 49:53.865
I'm not sure.

49:57.327 --> 49:59.246
I don't know what's okay

50:00.580 --> 50:02.499
and what is considered
"crossing the line."

50:05.210 --> 50:06.253
That's why

50:07.379 --> 50:08.422
this is frustrating.

50:11.091 --> 50:12.926
Then what do you want me to do?

50:16.847 --> 50:18.265
What can you do for me?

50:20.600 --> 50:21.893
No, don't cross.

50:28.525 --> 50:29.985
I don't think it's a good idea.

50:53.008 --> 50:54.426
- What took you so long?
- Hey.

50:55.552 --> 50:57.471
- Cheers, ladies.
- Cheers.

51:01.600 --> 51:02.934
- Let's order more.
- Excuse me.

51:03.018 --> 51:04.311
- We'll get two more.
- Sure.

51:11.276 --> 51:14.112
- Just get it over with.
- You think I don't want that?

52:47.747 --> 52:49.791
- Hello.
- Oh, hello.

52:51.376 --> 52:53.211
Did you call him? Shall I go get him?

52:53.587 --> 52:55.046
- He knows that I'm here.
- I see.

52:56.339 --> 52:58.925
How's your funny sister?
She's doing well, right?

53:00.051 --> 53:01.011
Yes.

53:02.929 --> 53:04.848
How are things with your friends? Good?

53:04.931 --> 53:06.141
Oh, yes. Of course.

53:08.852 --> 53:10.270
- There he is.
- Yes.

53:11.146 --> 53:12.522
Why didn't you wait inside?

53:14.107 --> 53:16.568
- Are you headed home?
- No, I'm meeting up with Ji-ho.

53:16.651 --> 53:18.904
For what?
Did something else happen to him?

53:19.362 --> 53:20.530
No, I don't think so.

53:21.698 --> 53:24.534
But I think he's going through stuff,
so I should check on him.

53:25.160 --> 53:28.330
I think we should find a nice lady
for him.

53:30.498 --> 53:33.251
You know what? My gut is telling me
that he has someone.

53:33.585 --> 53:34.794
Oh, you think so?

53:35.670 --> 53:36.963
That's great.

53:37.631 --> 53:39.257
Who's this girl he's seeing?

53:39.341 --> 53:42.093
That I don't know yet.
I shall interrogate him today.

53:44.221 --> 53:45.722
- All right, have fun.
- Will do.

53:47.057 --> 53:48.266
- Bye.
- Bye.

53:52.562 --> 53:53.605
Well...

53:55.148 --> 53:57.234
What's up?
Why did you come all the way here?

53:58.318 --> 53:59.319
No reason.

54:00.320 --> 54:01.863
Why? You don't like that I'm here?

54:03.615 --> 54:05.742
Look at you, all prickly again.

54:08.328 --> 54:09.663
All right. Where to?

54:11.456 --> 54:12.666
What's going on?

54:14.167 --> 54:15.293
Who is it?

54:16.044 --> 54:17.295
Just tell me who it is.

54:19.214 --> 54:20.215
It's a woman.

54:22.008 --> 54:23.301
Right, so who is this woman?

54:27.514 --> 54:29.891
She's just... A nice lady.

54:30.892 --> 54:31.935
Hey, seriously.

54:34.145 --> 54:35.146
Okay, fine.

54:35.981 --> 54:37.023
So, you like her.

54:37.649 --> 54:39.067
What do you like about her?

54:42.737 --> 54:44.406
It can't be explained in words.

54:45.824 --> 54:47.075
Look at you.

54:49.244 --> 54:51.329
I've never seen you this crazy before.

54:52.956 --> 54:54.499
I ended it before I get crazier.

54:56.334 --> 54:57.210
Already?

54:58.628 --> 54:59.629
Why?

55:00.880 --> 55:02.173
Then what? Should I go on?

55:04.092 --> 55:07.304
Jeez, you're so full of shit.

55:08.054 --> 55:09.472
It's obviously still ongoing.

55:10.682 --> 55:12.684
Right, I am working on ending it.

55:17.480 --> 55:18.690
What's the reason, though?

55:20.817 --> 55:22.694
Because I know how tough things will get.

55:24.821 --> 55:25.822
For you?

55:30.702 --> 55:31.745
For her.

55:43.089 --> 55:45.216
You really enjoyed it last time.

55:45.884 --> 55:47.552
I guess it's not as good today.

55:49.220 --> 55:50.221
It's good.

55:54.267 --> 55:55.852
Have you been taking the vitamins?

55:57.645 --> 55:58.688
Yes.

56:02.776 --> 56:04.903
How's Seo-in? Is she doing well?

56:06.529 --> 56:07.655
What do you mean?

56:08.323 --> 56:09.449
I'm just wondering

56:10.283 --> 56:12.077
if all is well between Si-hoon and her.

56:14.537 --> 56:16.581
All married couples have issues, you know.

56:20.752 --> 56:23.588
Is that why the idea of getting married
doesn't excite you?

56:26.758 --> 56:29.052
We decided to take some time
and think about it.

56:30.178 --> 56:31.846
I thought you had a change of heart.

56:36.267 --> 56:37.519
I'll try my best.

56:40.605 --> 56:41.856
Are we at a point where...

56:42.774 --> 56:44.692
we need to work on our relationship?

56:56.913 --> 56:58.081
Is there someone else?

57:15.390 --> 57:16.433
No, there isn't.

57:24.232 --> 57:25.066
No one?

57:26.276 --> 57:27.485
That's right.

57:28.570 --> 57:29.571
Are you sure?

57:31.739 --> 57:33.199
How can I prove it to you?

57:50.717 --> 57:51.759
Lies.

57:53.887 --> 57:54.971
What?

57:56.306 --> 57:57.432
Someone says...

58:00.393 --> 58:02.353
that she really hates lying,

58:05.148 --> 58:06.649
but she keeps lying to me.

58:06.733 --> 58:10.320
Hey, she sounds like a fraud.

58:11.946 --> 58:15.325
Hey, don't believe a word she says.

58:23.583 --> 58:24.626
Hyeon-su.

58:25.960 --> 58:27.003
What?

58:28.796 --> 58:30.215
Just once...

58:32.634 --> 58:34.010
Really, just one time...

58:37.889 --> 58:39.224
If I do whatever I want...

58:44.312 --> 58:46.147
I mean, if I follow my heart...

58:50.193 --> 58:51.486
will I be punished for it?

01:00:45.725 --> 01:00:48.144
- Hello.
- Oh, hello.

01:00:48.811 --> 01:00:50.021
It's been a while.

01:00:50.855 --> 01:00:52.231
Are you here to see Jeong-in?

01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:54.359
Yes, I am.

01:00:54.776 --> 01:00:57.153
But I didn't tell her.
I was just about to text her.

01:00:57.570 --> 01:00:59.656
You should surprise her. She's over there.

01:01:01.282 --> 01:01:02.367
Should I?

01:02:14.272 --> 01:02:15.314
Hey.

01:02:19.485 --> 01:02:20.737
Why are you so surprised?

01:02:57.064 --> 01:02:59.317
I'm so glad I got to know you.

01:02:59.400 --> 01:03:00.526
You're a good person.

01:03:00.610 --> 01:03:01.986
Remember my sister?

01:03:02.069 --> 01:03:04.113
When she sets her mind
on something she wants,

01:03:04.197 --> 01:03:05.782
no one in our family can stop her.

01:03:05.865 --> 01:03:08.242
Last time you talked about him,
I thought it was odd.

01:03:08.326 --> 01:03:09.494
Is something going on?

01:03:09.577 --> 01:03:11.746
You okay with me spending time
with another guy?

01:03:11.829 --> 01:03:12.997
Just a guy friend.

01:03:13.080 --> 01:03:15.625
I shouldn't betray Gi-seok, right?

01:03:15.708 --> 01:03:17.752
Gi-seok, shall we just get married?

01:03:18.252 --> 01:03:20.087
Gi-seok is finally getting hitched.

01:03:20.171 --> 01:03:21.464
What do you want me to do?

01:03:21.547 --> 01:03:24.550
- Do you want me to stop you?
- Why did you even come to the library?

01:03:24.634 --> 01:03:25.593
I wanted to see you.

01:03:25.676 --> 01:03:27.386
I won't expect anything from you,

01:03:27.470 --> 01:03:29.847
so just let me see you.
I promise I won't get caught.

01:03:29.931 --> 01:03:31.641
I understand how you feel, but--

01:03:31.724 --> 01:03:33.392
I won't get caught by you.

01:03:33.476 --> 01:03:35.603
Why are you avoiding me?
We didn't do anything.

01:03:35.686 --> 01:03:36.771
Let's talk in person.

01:03:36.896 --> 01:03:39.524
If you come to me now,
there's no going back.

01:03:42.193 --> 01:03:44.278
Subtitle translation by Liya Choi
